    <segment id="1" parent="2" relname="attribution">Hakken wrote, in part,</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="15" relname="span"> &quot;Two final points.  I believe we need
other philosophical resources on which to base a
reconstruction--I find them in emerging non-modernist forms of
realism (inspired by, e.g., Roy Bhaskar).  And we need to talk
concretely about the practices we project--e.g., not just
identify more democratic decisions about what technoscience to
pursue, but discuss specific mechanisms for how to accomplish
this. 

&quot;I know there are some scientist and technologists who are
willing to join such a discourse.  How to we reach others and
how do we create the forms in which to pursue it?&quot;</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="16" relname="span">

There is much food for thought here,</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="3" relname="elaboration"> and I would be very glad 
to join the discussion he proposes. </segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="17" relname="span"> One point for early 
attention is the extent to which the issues pursued by science 
are and should be based on democratic decisions.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="14" relname="span">  We have a lot 
of institutions that function (sometimes more, sometimes less 
well) in other ways. </segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="13" relname="span"> Think of the nuclear family,</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="7" relname="circumstance"> where votes 
are rare. </segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="6" relname="elaboration"> Or most churches, or the military, or how your 
doctor should treqt your very own next serious illness.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="18" relname="span">  Would 
any of these function better at the level of the big strategic 
decisions (equivalent to the choice of questions to be 
studied in science)</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="10" relname="condition"> if we made them democratic? </segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="19" relname="span"> I&apos;d like to 
see the arguments.</segment>
